    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-03-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-04-07T19:21:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Long-Term Care Trust Account Act of 2006 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) establish tax-exempt long-term care trust accounts; (2) allow cash contributions to such accounts up to $5,000 annually; (3) allow an exclusion from gross income for certain distributions, including for long-term care services for chronically-ill individuals; (4) impose penalties for excess contributions to such accounts and for failure to provide required reports on such accounts; and (5) allow a refundable tax credit for 10% of the annual contributions to such accounts. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
